: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">These breakthroughs keep ha=
ppening, and each time we&#8217;re like, &#8220;Oh yeah cool, oh well, ever=
ything still sucks.&#8221; Obviously, a big part of the reason for that is =
that technology isn&#8217;t the cure for everything, but c&#8217;mon. Self-=
driving cars are real and you can book one on your phone. That&#8217;s amaz=
ing.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26p=
x; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>There&#8217;s this thing where some people do=
n&#8217;t want to bring children into this terrible world of ours over fear=
s around climate change or whatever x-risk du jour terrifies them. Having k=
ids is a choice and to each their own, but if people genuinely aren&#8217;t=
 having kids because they&#8217;re worried about climate change, that&#8217=
;s fucking tragic. The kids will be alright, and if anything, our kids are =
going to feel bad for </span><em>us</em><span> for having to live in a worl=
d so primitive, like we feel bad for our grandparents for having to walk ei=
ght miles to and from school, in the snow, uphill both ways.&#160;</span></=
p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;"><span>I understand that things aren&#8217;t perfect today. Ther=
e&#8217;s inequality, disease, war, homelessness, drug addiction, prejudice=
, and, currently, this exhausting debate over the RFK Jr. debate, a little =
peek into our larger struggle with shared truths. Tech has not solved all o=
f the world&#8217;s problems as some of its boosters have promised it would=
 by now. But the answer is not to retreat and regress; </span><strong>the m=
oral imperative is to grow our way to the other side</strong><span>.</span>=
</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0 0 20px 0;"><span>This is not pollyannaish indefinite optimism. It is </s=
pan><strong>definite optimism</strong><span>.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"c=
olor: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">To =
be specific, the world Dev and Maya live in when they&#8217;re as old as Pu=
ja and I are now will be, conservatively, one with:&#160;</p><ul style=3D"m=
argin-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-f=
ormat: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: #404040; font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px=
;">Cheap, abundant energy, and all of the wonderful possibilities that enta=
ils,&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: b=
ullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: #404040; font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Fewer=
 diseases and longer healthy lives,&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px =
0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; =
color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-botto=
m: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Global connectivity for everyone on earth who wan=
ts it,</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bulle=
t;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: #404040; font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">On-demand=
 access to intelligence of all shapes and sizes,&#160;</p></li><li style=3D=
"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing:=
 border-box; color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;=
 margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">More broadly distributed ownership a=
nd governance of the products we use, and better access to financial opport=
unity for all,</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-forma=
t: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: #404040; font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">C=
heaper, faster travel on earth and to space and persistent access to rich, =
personalized and social virtual worlds,&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: =
8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-b=
ox; color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-b=
ottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Widespread availability of treatments for dep=
ression and finer tools to explore and expand the capabilities of their own=
 minds,&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format=
: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: #404040; font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Th=
e ability to grow an increasing percentage of the things they need biologic=
ally,</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet=
;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: #404040; font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Much, much=
 more, much of which we can&#8217;t possibly fathom today.&#160;</p></li></=
ul><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: =
0 0 20px 0;">This is the world in thirty years if even a fraction of the st=
artups today succeed. There will be thousands or millions of new startups f=
ormed in the interim, new technological breakthroughs to explore, and fasci=
nating opportunities opened up as many of today&#8217;s moonshots become ju=
mping-off points.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Just writing that list makes me so exc=
ited for Dev and Maya, and it makes me want to do everything I can to help =
speed it up. I want them to benefit from as much of this as possible, as qu=
ickly as possible, and I want to be there to help guide them through it. Se=
lfishly, part of the reason I&#8217;m an accelerationist is that I want Puj=
a and I to be able to live long enough to experience all of this magic with=
 them.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Of course, this future is not a foregone co=
nclusion. We can easily get in our own way. There are countless paths to sh=
ooting ourselves in the foot, from getting so caught up in petty bullshit t=
hat we take our eyes off the prize to letting bad actors taint promising te=
chnologies, but those seem tractable. The biggest risk to this future as I =
see it is that we do a bad job of bringing everyone along, incite backlash =
over every new innovation, and regulate ourselves to death, at least in the=
 United States. </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/39b50c42-a9=
ef-430b-85ff-f034006629c7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepK=
bqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: underline;=
">Nuclear</a><span> and </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/159=
28b43-3503-45d4-993f-94b472e40f5f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZ=
jmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: un=
derline;">psychedelics</a><span> are just two of many cautionary tales.</sp=
an></p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;">That dynamic is the reason that Not Boring&#8217;s mission=
 is to make the world more optimistic. It&#8217;s not so that we all feel b=
lindly and uselessly hopeful in the face of really bad things; it&#8217;s s=
o more people can see that the future, hopefully ours and definitely our ki=
ds&#8217;, is insanely bright if we let it be, and have the knowledge and e=
nthusiasm to fight on the side of that future.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: =
#404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>As =
I sat here writing this on Father&#8217;s Day, while my kids were playing o=
n the beach, I thought of </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/c=
0b6c853-d49e-4194-82a5-9e91e5aa1996?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNua=
MZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: #404040; text-decoration: =
underline;">the story of the investment banker and the fisherman</a><span>.=
 You know the story. There&#8217;s a fisherman who fishes a little every da=
y, siestas with his wife, spends time with his kids, and dances with his fr=
iends. An investment banker vacationing in town tells him that he could fis=
h more, expand, take on financing, make a lot of money, and then retire ear=
ly to fish a little every day, siesta with his wife, spend time with his ki=
ds, and dance with his friends.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: #404040;=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">It got me. I stop=
ped writing, went down to the beach, and played with my kids. There&#8217;s=
 no point in getting excited about living longer and being able to work les=
s if you already don&#8217;t get to enjoy the time you have with the people=
 you love.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-heigh=
t: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But they&#8217;re at the beach again, and I&#=
8217;m here writing. Unlike the fisherman, I don&#8217;t want the world to =
look the same when I retire as it does today.</p><div style=3D"font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px;"><hr style=3D"background: #e0e0e0; border: none; he=
ight: 1px; margin: 32px 0; padding: 0;"></div><p style=3D"color: #404040; f=
